---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Labs"
  description="Early interactive prototypes of the worldbuilding tool in development."
  hideTray={true}
>
  <h1>Labs</h1>
  <p>
    Working prototypes from the worldbuilding tool currently in design — a
    world wiki where every generator on this site can add a permanent, linked,
    editable page to <em>your</em> world, navigated from a world map that zooms
    from continent to dungeon. These are throwaway demos built to test design
    decisions, not the product; expect rough edges, and expect them to change.
  </p>

  <h2><a href="/world/">World wiki (alpha)</a></h2>
  <p>
    <strong>The real thing, first slice:</strong> create your own worlds, saved in
    your browser — linked pages, prompt-style fields, secrets, import/export.
    Built on the same schemas as the prototypes below.
  </p>

  <h2><a href="/labs/hex-zoom.html">Hex map zoom</a></h2>
  <p>
    The map concept: one continuous world under three hex tiers (60-mile,
    6-mile, 500-ft) that cross-fade as you zoom, Google-Maps style, down to a
    5-ft dungeon site. Every hex's terrain is generated from a seed on the
    fly — nothing you see is stored. Easiest way in: use the numbered
    <strong>tour buttons</strong> (World → Kingdom → Town → Tavern → Dungeon)
    and watch it dive. Then drag or touch-drag to pan; zoom with the wheel, a
    pinch, double-tap, or the +/− buttons; tap any hex to inspect it.
  </p>

  <h2><a href="/labs/world-viewer.html">World wiki editor</a></h2>
  <p>
    The wiki concept, seeded with a small test world ("Vessia") — and
    <strong>editable</strong>: rename pages, fill in prompt-style fields,
    write entries with live cross-links, mark blocks secret, and add new
    places, people, and factions inside any page. Your changes persist in
    your browser and export as JSON. Toggle <strong>Player View</strong> to
    watch secrets vanish, and open the tavern or the barrow to see
    battle-map floors with placed items.
  </p>

  <p>
    The full plans live in the repository under
    <a href="https://github.com/seriousd6/Storyteller/tree/main/docs/everdeep"
      >docs/everdeep</a
    >. Feedback is welcome —
    <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/seriousd6/">u/seriousd6</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
